point"],[931,"Endpoint"],[1269,"Endpoint"],[1070,"Environment variables"],[1029,"Environment variables `RUNYARD_HUB_URL` / `RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN` (and an explicit\n`--url` / `--token`) take precedence over the saved remote."],[793,"Error conventions"],[363,"Events, timeline, logs, artifacts"],[297,"Every budgeted run also carries a computed &#x2A;*`budgetStatus`** — spent vs limit, per dimension — so no client re-derives the arithmetic:"],[122,"Every card answers \"what will my decision do\" honestly, computed from what resolving actually performs:"],[310,"Every claude / codex / pi CLI call the Smithers engine reports via its structured `TokenUsageReported` events"],[458,"Every fire dispatches a normal run whose origin identifies the schedule:"],[820,"Every grouped operation is also reachable at a stable `/api/v1` alias that\nmakes the group visible in the path — for example:"],[151,"Every Hub URL is shareable - the hash-route grammar of the web app and the deep links the API returns."],[1268,"Every operation requires either a bearer access token (`Authorization: Bearer ...`) or a browser session created by exchanging such a token — and the session carries exactly the token's scopes, no extra power. The unauthenticated surface is deliberately tiny:"],[1231,"Every PR and push to `main` (and tags)"],[275,"Every run durably records not just what it produced, but **what it consumed**. Each model call a run's child agents make is captured as a usage record, streamed as a run event while the run executes, aggregated onto the run, and included in terminal payloads — so dashboards, delegated callers, and budget enforcement all work off real numbers, never log scraping."],[524,"Every Runyard API call is authenticated with a **bearer access token**:"],[796,"Every Runyard surface — the web app, the CLI, and the MCP server — is an\nordinary client of one HTTP API served by the Hub. Anything they can do, you\ncan do with `curl`."],[452,"Every schedule has an **IANA timezone** (default `UTC`); the expression is evaluated against wall-clock time in that zone, so DST shifts are honored."],[154,"Every URL in the Runyard web app is shareable: the app is a hash-routed SPA, so any view — a run's logs, a workflow's graph, a pending approval — can be copied from the address bar and opened by anyone with access to the Hub. Links have the form:"],[1147,"Everything durable is in the Hub's data directory (`RUNYARD_HUB_DATA_DIR`,\ndefault `data/`; the `hub-data` volume mounted at `/data` in containers). It\nsurvives every update and rollback:"],[540,"Everything. `admin` is a **superscope**: it satisfies every scope requirement, and admin-only endpoints (tokens, secrets, catalog edits, schedules, hooks, audit) require it."],[377,"Executing on the runner."],[253,"Execution"],[1402,"Execution engine; `\"smithers\"`."],[599,"Execution flow"],[1036,"Execution mode: `local` or `remote` (alias: `--execution-mode`)"],[1123,"Explicit SQLite database path (default `<data dir>/runyard.sqlite`)"],[359,"Failure classes"],[1313,"Failure classes"],[395,"Failures are classified into specific terminal statuses so operators can tell config problems from real failures: `failed` (generic), `blocked_by_gate` (a verification gate failed), `blocked_by_preflight` (the run could never start as configured), `provider_limited` (rate limits/quota), `timed_out`, `invalid_output` (schema mismatch), `infra_unavailable` (network/runner infrastructure), `needs_human`, and `budget_exceeded` (the run's metered usage reached its spend budget and it was hard-stopped)."],[113,"Field"],[679,"Field"],[1383,"Field"],[644,"Filters: `status`, `project`, `owner`, `type`, `q`; `includeArchived=true` shows archived."],[561,"Finer-grained per-group write scopes (e.g. a token that can manage schedules but not run workflows) are a documented follow-up; today `api`/`mcp` grant the whole operating surface."],[381,"Finished with outputs."],[485,"Fires immediately; rate-limited."],[1345,"Fix the runner host;