nt the workflow at it."],[362,"Preflight and run drafts (negotiation)"],[1314,"Preflight blockers"],[316,"Preflight blocks the run unless the selection is complete (pi harness, model, endpoint URL, and the Hub-secret name for the key) — a run never launches half-pinned. The endpoint key must be stored as a Hub secret; with gateway metering it is decrypted only inside the Hub per call and never enters the child environment."],[333,"Preflight checks this matching up front and reports `no_matching_runner` (blocker) or `runners_offline` (warning — the run would queue until one returns)."],[1040,"Preflight first: enqueue only when ready, otherwise print the negotiation state (questions/blockers and a saved draft) without creating a run"],[220,"Preflight rejects a request naming a profile that is disabled or not allowed for that workflow, so ineligible hooks surface before a run is created."],[499,"Preflight verifies every named secret exists before the run is enqueued. At **claim time** — when a runner claims the run — the Hub decrypts exactly those named secrets into an env map that rides the claim payload, and the runner injects them **only into the workflow's child process environment**. That is the sole path a plaintext value ever leaves the store:"],[543,"Preset"],[519,"Presets"],[611,"Priority, type, owner, and acceptance criteria clarified."],[1274,"Product name and version."],[1265,"Production posture"],[198,"Profiles are bounded on purpose"],[216,"Profiles reference secrets by **name only** (`secretNames`), declare typed `params` callers may fill, and can restrict which workflows may use them (`allowedCapabilities`)."],[454,"Provide `runAt` (an ISO timestamp) instead of `cron` to fire exactly once. A schedule takes one or the other."],[1103,"Provide secrets (`RUNYARD_HUB_SESSION_SECRET`, `SECRETS_ENC_KEY`,\n`RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN`, agent API keys) via a `.env` file or your platform's secret\nmechanism. For production, pin images by `@sha256:` digest rather than mutable\ntags. Optional overlays (all off by default):"],[307,"Provider key stays on the Hub; the child only holds a run-scoped gateway token"],[1119,"Public URL of the Hub (e.g. `https://hub.example.com`); an `https` value enables production behavior"],[696,"Published source lives in the Hub database as **workflow bundles**: immutable, hash-addressed rows in the `workflow_bundles` table. Publishing is insert-only — every publish creates a new `(workflow slug, version)` row with a `sha256` of the source, so a bundle id permanently names the exact bytes that were published. Bundles are capped at 500 KB, listing never returns source bytes, and a workflow that references a missing bundle fails preflight rather than silently falling back to a file."],[1238,"Publishes the GitHub Release with generated notes — only after `test` and `sandbox-smoke` are green. A red run never publishes."],[680,"Purpose"],[845,"Purpose"],[876,"Purpose"],[893,"Purpose"],[908,"Purpose"],[998,"Purpose"],[1270,"Purpose"],[209,"Push a work branch to a configured remote. Protected branches (`main`, `master`) are refused — merging to the default branch stays behind explicit run promotion."],[753,"Push instead of poll: response endpoints"],[1237,"Pushed `v*` tags"],[1240,"Pushed `v*` tags"],[468,"Query: `cron`, `timezone`."],[1064,"Quick install (host bootstrap)"],[11,"Quickstart"],[794,"Rate limits"],[609,"Raw ask, idea, bug, or product need."],[916,"Re-preflight and enqueue the real run only when ready — `202` with `{run, draft}`"],[1339,"Re-run; if recurring, raise the workflow's time budget or shrink the job."],[1330,"Read the run logs for the gate output; fix the underlying work and re-run."],[1348,"Read the run output and the linked approval/escalation card."],[57,"Reading any catalog requires only an authenticated token. Creating and updating entries requires the `admin` scope — the catalogs are part of the Hub's trusted configuration, like secrets and hook profiles."],[1053,"Reads available to any token: `runyard runners` (runner pool), `runyard agents`,\n`runyard skills`, `runyard knowledge -q <query>`, `runyard hooks [--workflow <slug>]`, and `runyard hook describe|validate <slug>`. Secrets have\nno CLI subcommand — manage them in the web UI, over the\nAPI (`PUT /api/secrets/:key`), or with the MCP `set_secret` tool."],[814,"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, or artifacts require any authenticated\ntoken. A token with only the `read` scope is therefore read-only: it can\ninspect everything non-admin but every create/update/delete/run/approve call\nfails with `403`. A request with no valid token gets\n`401 {\"error\": \"unauthorized\"}`; a token missing a required scope gets:"],[541,"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, runners, or schedules need only an authenticated token, whatever its scopes. Runner lifecycle endpoints additionally enforce **run ownership**: only the runner token that claimed a run (or an admin) may report on it."],[373,"Ready for a matching runner to claim."],[1235,"Real bubblewrap + AppArmor gate on Ubuntu 24.04: installs bwrap, loads the repo's AppArmor profile via the same script operators run, then runs the sandbox suites with `RUNYARD_REQUIRE_BWRAP=1` so the smoke test fails rather than skips."],[752,"Recommended agent etiquette"],[1161,"Recommended agent flow"],[277,"Records fold into the run's persisted aggregate the moment they arrive:"],[984,"Records that the run should be left as it ended."],[983,"Records that the workflow or input needs fixing; your note is the guidance."],[982,"Records your go-ahead on the card; the run is not restarted — re-run it from the run page."],[54,"Reference resources — documents or links with a type, body/URL, and tags — searchable with `?q=` / `search_knowledge`."],[688,"References into the shared catalog."],[880,"Registered runners, heartbeat state, capacity, pool summary"],[319,"Registration, heartbeat, claim"],[972,"Reject"],[903,"Reject — a held run is cancelled (never failed)"],[1049,