re never failed or reaped for waiting. Find and resolve the card — web **Approvals**, `runyard approvals` then `runyard approve|reject|request-changes <approval-id>`, or the MCP tools. See Approvals."],[356,"The run lifecycle, preflight and run drafts, events and artifacts, reruns, and promotion."],[1091,"The runner authenticates with a runner-scoped token (`RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN`); on a\nfresh Hub it may use the bootstrap token until you mint one."],[294,"The runner observes the terminal status on its next poll and cancels the detached engine run, and the gateway refuses further calls from that run's token (`403`)."],[354,"The runner protocol endpoints intentionally have no MCP tools — they are Hub↔runner machinery, not an operator surface."],[808,"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle events and artifacts"],[536,"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle, upload artifacts."],[1292,"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle."],[1332,"The runner's preflight refused to execute (missing workflow source, auth not ready, repo path problems)."],[36,"The same data lives at `GET /api/runs/{id}`, `/api/runs/{id}/timeline`, `/api/runs/{id}/logs`, and `/api/runs/{id}/artifacts`, and in the web run page — the Hub is the source of truth even when execution happened on a local runner."],[532,"The same operating surface for MCP clients."],[1290,"The same operations over the MCP server."],[804,"The same operations, issued for MCP clients"],[23,"The script never prints secrets, never applies updates automatically, and prints a Caddy reverse-proxy snippet if you want TLS in front (recommended for anything non-local — see the security guide)."],[1172,"The server exposes **87 tools**, generated from the same API surface registry\nthe Hub's routes and `/openapi.json` come from. Grouped by resource:"],[1167,"The server name is `runyard` for the default remote and `runyard-<remote>` for\nothers, so one